               <head>Commonplace book including notes on Old Testament books; Germany, 15th century</head>
               <msContents>
                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Hamilton_40-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1r–128v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_15254" type="desc">Commonplace book</title>
                     <note> consisting of excerpts from various works of theology and morals, including (fols. 101a recto – e verso) an alphabetical index of subjects, Abscondit se – Ymago dei. </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" xml:id="MS_Hamilton_40-item2">
                     <locus>(fols. 129r-288v)</locus>
                     <title key="work_12046" type="desc">Glosses on the Old Testament and Apocrypha</title>
                     <note>(<ref target="http://www.repbib.uni-trier.de/cgi-bin/rebiIndex.tcl?ac=searchlist&amp;tlnr=10150">Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 10150</ref>)</note>
                     <note>Excepting the Pentateuch; in confused order (starting with Jeremiah and Lamentations, ending with Judges and Joshua.</note>
                     <rubric>Prologus in Ieremiam prophetam</rubric>
                     <incipit>Fuit enim Anathotites, qui est usque hodie viculus tribus ab Ierosolymis distans milibus</incipit>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="chart">
                        <support>paper</support>
                        <extent> ii (medieval parchment) + 352 leaves + i (medieval parchment) <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height max="155" min="145">145–155</height>
                              <width>105</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation>Medieval foliation in back and red inks, 1–289, but with numerous gaps and inserted leaves, necessitating duplicate folio numbers in modern pencil, recorded as: ‘Really 352 for pp 26, 32, 40, 49, 50, 52, 54, 59, 71, 75, 76, 78, 83, 96, 117, 127, 133, 134, 147, 148, 149, 150, 151, 152, 153, 159, 163, 165, 167, 169, 170, 178, 179, 180, 181, 185, 187, 191, 193, 194, 195, 216, 236, 242, 244, 247, 248, 249, 250, 267 and 273 are double; pp. 47 &amp; 195 are treble; page 101 is fivefold and p. 201 is sevenfold’ </foliation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="1" writtenLines="31 35">Verticals (only) ruled in ink, written in 1 col., typically of 31–35 lines. Written space varies, typically <dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
                              <height max="135" min="120">120–135</height>
                              <width max="80" min="70">70–80</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
