                        <note><title>Compilatio tertia decretalium</title> with commentary, upper part of a leaf</note>
                        <msItem>
                           <title key="work_16400">Compilatio tertia decretalium</title>
                           <rubric>Idem illustri regi Navarie</rubric>
                           <incipit>Ad audienciam nostram</incipit>
                           <rubric>Idem illustri regi aringonen.</rubric>
                           <incipit>Quanto personam tuam</incipit>
                           <note>Fol. ii verso has the end of II.xv.2 and the beginning of II.xv.3; fol. ii recto has the end of II.xv.3 and (presumably) part of II.xv.4 (<title>Quinque compilationes</title>, ed. Friedberg, 114–5); cf. Innocent III, ep. I.556 (PL 214.509); the fragment before fol. i has (on the verso) the beginning of II.xv.4</note>
                        </msItem>
